FBIS4-46173 "jptot022__l94082" JPRS-TOT-94-022-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 27 May 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA MOLDOVA Dniester Procurator Injured in Assassination Attempt Dniester Procurator Injured in Assassination Attempt Luchik Had Received Threats AU2705120894 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 1000 GMT 27 May 94 AU2705120894 Bucharest Radio Romania Network Romanian BFN [Text] Radio Moldova has reported that yesterday there was a powerful explosion in a building in the center of Tiraspol. Citing a communique released by the press center of the ministry of security [of the Dniester republic] which had been broadcast by Radio Tiraspol, Radio Moldova announced that the targets of the terrorist attack were the prosecutor of the self-proclaimed Dniester republic, Boris Luchik, his wife, and two of his bodyguards. According to unofficial information, one of the bodyguards died, while the health of Luchik's wife is critical. After first describing the explosion as a terrorist act intended to destabilize the political situation in the Dniester region, the communique released today by the ministry of security asserts that Luchik had received repeated anonymous telephone threats. According to the same sources, the prosecutor of the self-proclaimed Dniester republic has initiated criminal proceedings against Col. Bergman [General Mikhail Bergman, chief of staff of the Dniester separatist forces] and now the latter seems to be trying to settle accounts with Luchik.
